 &lt;img src="https://mpov.timmorgan.org/images/ipad_and_printer.jpg" alt="Dymo printer next to iPad running Planning Center Check-Ins" /&gt;
&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="first-some-background"&gt;First, some background &lt;a href="#first-some-background" class="anchor"&gt;🔗&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;My church uses &lt;a href="https://www.planningcenter.com/check-ins" target="_blank" rel="noopener"&gt;Planning Center Check-Ins&lt;/a&gt; to track attendance for churchgoers, and to help with security with little ones going to kids areas. It&amp;rsquo;s a great product. &lt;strong&gt;Yay!&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Check-Ins runs on iOS, Android, macOS, and Windows machines. &lt;strong&gt;Yay!&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.dymo.com/en-US/dymo-labeling-needs/mailing-shipping-labeling/mailing-shipping-labeling/labelwriter-450-label-printer" target="_blank" rel="noopener"&gt;Dymo label printers&lt;/a&gt; are cheap and plentiful. &lt;strong&gt;Yay!&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Check-Ins can print to a Dymo printer from macOS or Windows, but not from a tablet. &lt;strong&gt;Boo!&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description></item></channel></rss>